  "prompt": "When and how did Ambrose Bierce die?",
  "response": "The exact details of Ambrose Bierce's death are unknown and remain a mystery. In late 1913, Bierce, who was in his early seventies, traveled to Mexico, which was in the midst of a revolution. He intended to witness the Mexican Revolution firsthand and reportedly joined Pancho Villa's forces as an observer. Bierce sent a final letter from Chihuahua, Mexico, in December 1913. After that, there were no confirmed reports of his whereabouts or fate. Various theories suggest he might have been killed in battle, executed, or succumbed to illness, but none have been substantiated. As a result, his disappearance adds a layer of intrigue to his legacy as a writer and journalist.",
